@startuml
' Caption: High-level context showing how instructors and students interact with AutoSlide and which external systems it depends on.
title AutoSlide System Context

left to right direction
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

actor Instructor
actor Student
actor "Institutional LMS / Admin\n(optional)" as LMS

component "PowerPoint + VSTO Add-in" as Addin
component "AutoSlide Backend" as Backend
component "AutoSlide Web Portal / Viewer" as Web
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
component "File Storage\n(Supabase / uploads)" as Storage
cloud "External LLM API" as LLM

Instructor --> Addin : create / run live session
Addin --> Backend : upload PPTX, ink, transcript\nstart / end / slide updates
Backend --> DB : persist users, courses,\nsessions, materials
Backend --> Storage : store PPTX, PDFs,\ntranscripts, summaries
Backend --> LLM : on-demand summary request\nfrom replay / history
Student --> Web : join live session,\nview replay, download materials
Web --> Backend : HTTPS + SignalR +\nsummary request
LMS ..> Backend : course / roster provisioning
@enduml